[2] Cholera - Dominican Republic
Date: Sat 19 Feb 2011
Source: NAM News Network (NNN), Prensa Latina [edited]
<http://www.namnewsnetwork.org/v2/read.php?id=148771>


This week, 21 cases of cholera were reported in different parts of the
country, the Ministry of Public Health reported Fri 18 Feb 2011, in a
communique.

During the week, 72 people suspected of having contracted cholera were
studied, but only 21 were positive.

Health authorities said they maintain an all out surveillance with
prevention and control measures against the disease throughout the
country.

The communique placed particular emphasis on the hygienic measures to
prevent the disease and urged the population to go to the nearest
health facility if they have any symptoms.

--
