[4] Cholera - Papua New Guinea
Date: Wed 16 Feb 2011
Source: Radio New Zealand International [edited]
<http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=58801>


Papua New Guinea's top health official says nearly 500 people have
died from the country's prolonged cholera outbreak. The health
secretary, Dr Clement Malau, has told the newspaper, The National,
that 483 people have died while more than 10 000 have been diagnosed
with cholera since the 1st outbreak in August 2009 in Morobe Province.

So far, 7 regions, including the capital Port Moresby, have been
affected by cholera with Dr Malau saying Western Province was the
worst hit with 300 deaths.

--
